"The UNIX operating system for PDP11 computers was purchased from
Western Electric-Bell Laboratories in May 1977.  This system will be
used to control data base access and graphics facilities on the satellite
PDP11/45 computer."
Australian Atomic Energy Commission, Research Establishment
Nuclear Science and Technology Branch Report 1977
Research Establishment Site Management, December 1977, p 41
AAEC/PR44-S
https://inis.iaea.org/records/0y6mm-22f39

"The UNIX operating system, developed by Bell Laboratories in the United
States for large DEC PDP11 computers, has been used as a base from which to
provide a wide range of interactive user facilities for both the PDP11/45
Graphics node and the Site Information Services (SIS) PDP11/34 computer.
Access is also available to the Editorial and Publications Group for the
preparation of technical documents (see Sections 2.4 and 5.5)

An international symposium on language design and programming methodology
held in September 1979 was organised by Division staff and sponsored jointly
by the Commission and the University of New South Wales.  This symposium
attracted world-wide interest, with keynote speakers coming from Austria
and the United States."  
Australian Atomic Energy Commission, Research Establishment
Progress Report 1979, December 1980, pp 6-7
AAEC/PR46, Part I
https://inis.iaea.org/records/f5d0e-3g559
